    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker** headlining our offensive strategy. **Gunnar Henderson** is our premier play at an 83.29, benefiting from a potent combination of a top-tier leadoff spot, a favorable matchup against Wacha, and a wind boost that amplifies his power profile. **Kyle Tucker** (81.77) remains a high-floor, high-ceiling anchor; he faces Mahle in conditions favorable for hitters, and his underlying xwOBA metrics suggest he is due for a positive regression in run production. **Jackson Merrill** also presents significant upside today (75.10) as he benefits from a 14% park factor boost and a favorable matchup against Sugano, making him a critical piece of our pursuit of league-leading counting stats.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was undoubtedly **Marcell Ozuna** (60.81). While he cleared our \"Strong\" threshold for starting, the overall efficiency scores of our depth necessitated his exclusion. **Marcell Ozuna** remains a high-value asset, but he narrowly lost out to the platoon advantages held by the likes of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**\u2014who draws a highly favorable matchup against Fuentes (5.07 xERA)\u2014and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, whose underlying quality of contact remains elite despite a neutral platoon stance against Soriano. We continue to monitor the risk profiles for **Jacob Wilson** (40.47) and **Heliot Ramos** (40.72), as both face elite, low-xERA arms in Gilbert and Ohtani, respectively. Should these contests tilt toward the pitchers early, we are prepared to utilize our bench depth, including **Coby Mayo** and **Nolan Schanuel**, to maintain our efficiency mandates and preserve our precious games-played cap.",
